{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-11",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_11_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "11 - Who Stole the Tarts?",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 1.488,
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 3,
  "page_start_sec": 251.16,
  "page_end_sec": 491.28,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 251.16,
      "end": 252.2,
      "text": "Write that down,"
    },
    {
      "start": 252.42,
      "end": 253.76,
      "text": "the king said to the jury,"
    },
    {
      "start": 253.86,
      "end": 257.1,
      "text": "and the jury eagerly wrote down all three dates on their slates,"
    },
    {
      "start": 257.14,
      "end": 258.24,
      "text": "and then added them up,"
    },
    {
      "start": 258.32,
      "end": 260.66,
      "text": "and reduced the answer to shillings and pence."
    },
    {
      "start": 261.38,
      "end": 262.14,
      "text": "Take off your hat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 262.32,
      "end": 263.66,
      "text": "the king said to the hatter."
    },
    {
      "start": 264.46,
      "end": 265.06,
      "text": "It isn't mine,"
    },
    {
      "start": 265.34,
      "end": 266.16,
      "text": "said the hatter."
    },
    {
      "start": 266.9,
      "end": 267.36,
      "text": "Stolen,"
    },
    {
      "start": 267.66,
      "end": 268.7,
      "text": "the king exclaimed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 268.7,
      "end": 269.72,
      "text": "turning to the jury,"
    },
    {
      "start": 269.86,
      "end": 272.02,
      "text": "who instantly made a memorandum of the fact."
    },
    {
      "start": 273.28,
      "end": 274.34,
      "text": "I keep them to sell,"
    },
    {
      "start": 274.6,
      "end": 276.22,
      "text": "the hatter added as an explanation."
    },
    {
      "start": 276.52,
      "end": 277.78,
      "text": "I've none of my own."
    },
    {
      "start": 277.86,
      "end": 278.58,
      "text": "I'm a hatter."
    },
    {
      "start": 280.16,
      "end": 281.94,
      "text": "Here the queen put on her spectacles,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 282.0,
      "end": 284.18,
      "text": "and began staring hard at the hatter,"
    },
    {
      "start": 284.26,
      "end": 285.96,
      "text": "who turned pale and fidgeted."
    },
    {
      "start": 287.24,
      "end": 287.86,
      "text": "Give your evidence,"
    },
    {
      "start": 288.18,
      "end": 289.0,
      "text": "said the king,"
    },
    {
      "start": 289.12,
      "end": 290.04,
      "text": "and don't be nervous,"
    },
    {
      "start": 290.34,
      "end": 291.86,
      "text": "or I'll have you executed on the spot."
    },
    {
      "start": 292.8,
      "end": 294.9,
      "text": "This did not seem to encourage the witness at all."
    },
    {
      "start": 294.96,
      "end": 297.14,
      "text": "He kept shifting from one foot to the other,"
    },
    {
      "start": 297.24,
      "end": 298.8,
      "text": "looking uneasily at the queen,"
    },
    {
      "start": 299.18,
      "end": 301.42,
      "text": "and in his confusion he bit a large piece out"
    },
    {
      "start": 301.42,
      "end": 303.26,
      "text": "of his teacup instead of the bread and butter."
    },
    {
      "start": 304.48,
      "end": 305.36,
      "text": "Just at this moment,"
    },
    {
      "start": 305.52,
      "end": 307.58,
      "text": "Alice felt a very curious sensation,"
    },
    {
      "start": 307.86,
      "end": 309.62,
      "text": "which puzzled her a good deal until"
    },
    {
      "start": 309.62,
      "end": 310.7,
      "text": "she made out what it was."
    },
    {
      "start": 310.96,
      "end": 313.0,
      "text": "She was beginning to grow larger again,"
    },
    {
      "start": 313.16,
      "end": 314.44,
      "text": "and she thought at first she"
    },
    {
      "start": 314.44,
      "end": 315.62,
      "text": "would get up and leave the court,"
    },
    {
      "start": 316.14,
      "end": 319.16,
      "text": "but on second thoughts she decided to remain where she was as"
    },
    {
      "start": 319.16,
      "end": 320.26,
      "text": "long as there was room for her."
    },
    {
      "start": 321.18,
      "end": 323.24,
      "text": "I wish you wouldn't squeeze so,"
    },
    {
      "start": 323.46,
      "end": 324.4,
      "text": "said the Dormouse,"
    },
    {
      "start": 324.5,
      "end": 324.92,
      "text": "who was sitting"
    },
    {
      "start": 325.04,
      "end": 325.48,
      "text": "next to her."
    },
    {
      "start": 325.54,
      "end": 326.66,
      "text": "I can hardly breathe."
    },
    {
      "start": 327.14,
      "end": 328.58,
      "text": "I can't help it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 328.66,
      "end": 329.9,
      "text": "said Alice very meekly."
    },
    {
      "start": 329.9,
      "end": 330.36,
      "text": "I'm growing."
    },
    {
      "start": 332.02,
      "end": 333.08,
      "text": "You've no right to grow here,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 333.32,
      "end": 334.46,
      "text": "said the Dormouse."
    },
    {
      "start": 335.392,
      "end": 336.22,
      "text": "Don't talk nonsense,"
    },
    {
      "start": 336.62,
      "end": 337.8,
      "text": "said Alice more boldly."
    },
    {
      "start": 338.54,
      "end": 339.7,
      "text": "You know you're growing too."
    },
    {
      "start": 340.52,
      "end": 340.78,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 340.82,
      "end": 342.42,
      "text": "but I grow at a reasonable pace,"
    },
    {
      "start": 342.7,
      "end": 343.68,
      "text": "said the Dormouse."
    },
    {
      "start": 344.256,
      "end": 345.6,
      "text": "Not in that ridiculous fashion."
    },
    {
      "start": 346.38,
      "end": 348.32,
      "text": "And he got up very sulkily and crossed"
    },
    {
      "start": 348.32,
      "end": 349.94,
      "text": "over to the other side of the court."
    },
    {
      "start": 351.84,
      "end": 354.98,
      "text": "All this time the Queen had never left off staring at the Hatter,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 355.34,
      "end": 357.28,
      "text": "and just as the Dormouse crossed the court,"
    },
    {
      "start": 357.72,
      "end": 359.72,
      "text": "she said to one of the officers of the court,"
    },
    {
      "start": 360.11,
      "end": 363.46,
      "text": "Bring me the list of the singers in the last concert,"
    },
    {
      "start": 364.36,
      "end": 366.0,
      "text": "on which the wretched Hatter trembled"
    },
    {
      "start": 366.0,
      "end": 368.18,
      "text": "so that he shook off both of his shoes."
    },
    {
      "start": 369.88,
      "end": 370.46,
      "text": "Give your evidence,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 370.76,
      "end": 372.28,
      "text": "the king repeated angrily,"
    },
    {
      "start": 372.3,
      "end": 373.34,
      "text": "or I'll have you executed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 373.56,
      "end": 374.74,
      "text": "whether you're nervous or not."
    },
    {
      "start": 376.5,
      "end": 377.22,
      "text": "I'm a poor man,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 377.4,
      "end": 377.82,
      "text": "your majesty,"
    },
    {
      "start": 378.6,
      "end": 380.26,
      "text": "the Hatter began in a trembling voice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 380.38,
      "end": 382.38,
      "text": "and I hadn't begun my tea,"
    },
    {
      "start": 382.56,
      "end": 383.92,
      "text": "not above a week or so,"
    },
    {
      "start": 384.4,
      "end": 386.8,
      "text": "and what with the bread and butter getting so thin,"
    },
    {
      "start": 386.92,
      "end": 388.32,
      "text": "and the twinkling of the tea."
    },
    {
      "start": 389.02,
      "end": 390.06,
      "text": "The twinkling of the what?"
    },
    {
      "start": 390.29,
      "end": 391.08,
      "text": "said the king."
    },
    {
      "start": 392.42,
      "end": 393.76,
      "text": "It began with the tea,"
    },
    {
      "start": 394.56,
      "end": 395.16,
      "text": "the hatter replied."
    },
    {
      "start": 396.26,
      "end": 398.02,
      "text": "Of course twinkling begins with a tea,"
    },
    {
      "start": 398.26,
      "end": 399.12,
      "text": "said the king sharply."
    },
    {
      "start": 399.46,
      "end": 400.48,
      "text": "Do you take me for a dunce?"
    },
    {
      "start": 400.98,
      "end": 401.26,
      "text": "Go on."
    },
    {
      "start": 402.816,
      "end": 403.56,
      "text": "I'm a poor man,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 404.06,
      "end": 404.82,
      "text": "the hatter went on,"
    },
    {
      "start": 404.92,
      "end": 407.0,
      "text": "and most things twinkled after that."
    },
    {
      "start": 407.32,
      "end": 408.46,
      "text": "Only the March Hare said."
    },
    {
      "start": 409.24,
      "end": 409.82,
      "text": "I didn't,"
    },
    {
      "start": 409.82,
      "end": 411.68,
      "text": "the March Hare interrupted in a great hurry."
    },
    {
      "start": 412.52,
      "end": 412.82,
      "text": "You did,"
    },
    {
      "start": 413.08,
      "end": 413.84,
      "text": "said the hatter."
    },
    {
      "start": 414.34,
      "end": 415.04,
      "text": "I deny it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 415.12,
      "end": 415.98,
      "text": "said the March Hare."
    },
    {
      "start": 416.7,
      "end": 417.84,
      "text": "He denies it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 417.92,
      "end": 418.52,
      "text": "said the King."
    },
    {
      "start": 418.7,
      "end": 419.6,
      "text": "Leave out that part."
    },
    {
      "start": 420.32,
      "end": 420.58,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 420.7,
      "end": 421.4,
      "text": "at any rate,"
    },
    {
      "start": 421.48,
      "end": 422.38,
      "text": "the Dormouse said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 422.54,
      "end": 423.58,
      "text": "the Hatter went on,"
    },
    {
      "start": 423.62,
      "end": 426.12,
      "text": "looking anxiously round to see if he would deny it too,"
    },
    {
      "start": 426.4,
      "end": 427.7,
      "text": "but the Dormouse denied nothing,"
    },
    {
      "start": 427.9,
      "end": 428.74,
      "text": "being fast asleep."
    },
    {
      "start": 430.08,
      "end": 430.48,
      "text": "After that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 430.7,
      "end": 431.6,
      "text": "continued the Hatter,"
    },
    {
      "start": 431.68,
      "end": 433.12,
      "text": "I cut some more bread and butter."
    },
    {
      "start": 434.22,
      "end": 435.56,
      "text": "But what did the Dormouse say,"
    },
    {
      "start": 435.72,
      "end": 436.66,
      "text": "one of the jury asked."
    },
    {
      "start": 437.568,
      "end": 438.5,
      "text": "That I can't remember,"
    },
    {
      "start": 438.72,
      "end": 439.36,
      "text": "said the Hatter."
    },
    {
      "start": 440.28,
      "end": 441.02,
      "text": "You must remember,"
    },
    {
      "start": 441.34,
      "end": 442.0,
      "text": "remarked the King,"
    },
    {
      "start": 442.1,
      "end": 443.36,
      "text": "or I'll have you executed."
    },
    {
      "start": 444.62,
      "end": 447.6,
      "text": "the miserable hatter dropped his tea-cup and bread and"
    },
    {
      "start": 447.6,
      "end": 451.54,
      "text": "butter and went down on one knee i'm a poor man your"
    },
    {
      "start": 451.54,
      "end": 455.88,
      "text": "majesty he began you're a very poor speaker said the king"
    },
    {
      "start": 457.02,
      "end": 459.14,
      "text": "here one of the guinea-pigs cheered and was"
    },
    {
      "start": 459.14,
      "end": 461.64,
      "text": "immediately suppressed by the officers of the court"
    },
    {
      "start": 462.58,
      "end": 464.4,
      "text": "as that is rather a hard word i will"
    },
    {
      "start": 464.4,
      "end": 465.96,
      "text": "just explain to you how it was done"
    },
    {
      "start": 466.56,
      "end": 469.7,
      "text": "they had a large canvas bag which tied up at the mouth with strings"
    },
    {
      "start": 469.83,
      "end": 473.18,
      "text": "into this they slipped the guinea-pig head first and then sat upon it"
    },
    {
      "start": 473.88,
      "end": 475.04,
      "text": "I'm glad I've seen that done,"
    },
    {
      "start": 475.22,
      "end": 475.7,
      "text": "thought Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 475.88,
      "end": 478.72,
      "text": "I've so often read in the newspapers at the end of"
    },
    {
      "start": 478.8,
      "end": 481.22,
      "text": "trials there was some attempt at applause which"
    },
    {
      "start": 481.22,
      "end": 483.48,
      "text": "was immediately suppressed by the officers of"
    },
    {
      "start": 483.48,
      "end": 483.88,
      "text": "the court,"
    },
    {
      "start": 484.0,
      "end": 485.98,
      "text": "and I never understood what it meant till now."
    },
    {
      "start": 487.75,
      "end": 489.42,
      "text": "If that's all you know about it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 489.46,
      "end": 490.26,
      "text": "you may stand down,"
    },
    {
      "start": 490.38,
      "end": 491.28,
      "text": "continued the king."
    }
  ]
}